<head>
<title>CSS Test: Height of root element</title>
  <link rel="author" title="Ian Hickson" href="mailto:ian@hixie.ch"/>
  <link rel="alternate" href="http://www.hixie.ch/tests/adhoc/css/background/14.html" type="text/html"/>
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS2/visudet.html#Computing_heights_and_margins"/>
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#containing-block-details"/>
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/colors.html#background"/>
<style type="text/css">
   body { border: solid lime; background: green; color: white; }
   html { border: solid blue; background: navy; color: yellow; }
   :link, :visited { color: inherit; background: transparent; }
   * { margin: 1em; padding: 1em; }
</style>

</head>
<body>
<p> The inner box (BODY) should be green, it should be bordered in
bright green. The inner box should centred inside a blue box (HTML)
with a bright blue border. The blue box (HTML) should itself be in a
sea of blue: the canvas, whose background is the same as the HTML
element's. The outer sea of blue should be the size of the viewport,
but the inner boxes should just wrap around this text. The HTML box
SHOULD NOT SIZE TO FIT THE VIEWPORT!</p>


</body>
</html>
